comments.text:
Super Mario 64 has a ton of nuance to it that many people don't understand. The character development, albeit shallow looking at a surface level, is actually genius. It not only subverts the expectations of the character tropes that many of the characters fall under, but also leaves plenty of social commentary for the player to digest. Said commentary explaining the problem with needless escapism through video games while being within the medium itself is absolutely genius, and said genius is why nobody got it when it came out back in '96. But thankfully with the advent of forums like MarioGeeks and several internet analyses which point out everything with the game's story and characters, many people have finally gotten the message, even 26 years later.

Great remix by the way. Shame it took me this long to find it though.
